originalText.text:
It's really true .. TD makes a big deal about being friendly and customer focused in its advertising and I have to agree completely.

I've been in a number of branches in Manhattan and they are all as good as this one ... wonderful hours and great service plus always free pens and candy.

Atms are great too ... I really use them most of the time but the few occasions when I've gone inside the branch, service is always the best.

originalText.text:
Nice professional and comfortable.

They got some new faces and the place looked better managed this time than my previous visit several months ago. All I needed today was to print out a card so I decided to give it a second try and it's on my way back from Wholefoods anyway. Now I am glad I did. Alan is very helpful, efficient, and business appropriate. I don't know why, most of the time, everywhere I go things seem normal to me. I rarely got pissed off.

Anyway, nice

originalText.text: The worst customer service I have ever experienced from a supervisor. After giving up waiting on the phone over a half hour with customer service, I called this branch and unfortunately got this supervisor named Natasha who was rude, confrontational and argumentative. All she needed to do was resolve my simple issue, but instead told me "no, no, no" constantly talking over me. After an unnecessary combative conversation I was shocked and horrified by the nightmarish customer service experience. Completely unacceptable. Avoid this branch at all costs.

originalText.text: Friendly and corteous service, especially the one teller I had. She went out of her way to be helpful and greeted me with the most beautiful smile I have ever seen behind a plexiglass window. Very cautious with Covid hygiene and protocol which I appreciated.

originalText.text: I went there this afternoon to make a cash deposit. I usually use the ATM machine for small amounts but this time I was carrying close to a grand in 20 dollar bills so I planned on waiting in line for the teller, just to be safe. (I didn't wanna take a chance on the machine not counting my money properly and having to dispute, etc.) But then a very pleasant female associate offered to help and assured me that I'd have no problems with using the ATM to make the deposit. I even joked, asking if she really was a TD bank employee, because she offered to physically check the condition of my bills --if there were staples, or if they were folded/torn -- before I fed them into the machine. She explained how to avoid problems with the ATM. I can't recall her name exactly, it sounded unusual for me..but I think it starts with an S...like Shezallia or something like that. But I think her desk is the first to your right when you enter. She is the epitome of customer service! Keep up the good work!
